  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:&amp;quot;PT Sans&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px&quot;&gt;The\r\n proposed advertisement, by reason of its scale, siting, appearance, and \r\nmethod of illumination would result in an excessive and obtrusive feature that contributes to an unsightly proliferation of signage and street furniture in the local area. The proposal therefore\r\ndetracts from the visual amenity of the street scene. As such, the \r\nproposal is considered unacceptable and fails to comply with policies D4 (Delivering Good Design) and \r\nD8 (Public Realm) of the London Plan (2021) and policies PP1 (Public \r\nRealm), LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character),&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;and LP7 (Advertisements) of Hackney&#x27;s Local Plan LP33 (2020).&lt;/p&gt;",
    "&lt;p&gt;The\r\n proposed advertisement, by reason of its appearance and illumination and proximity to the public highway, would result in an obstructive and intrusive form of \r\ndevelopment that would reduce the legibility of the footpath by blocking lines of sight and creating distractions for highway users to the detriment of highway safety. As such the proposed development is contrary \r\nto policies D8 (Public Realm) and&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-variant-position: normal; vertical-align: baseline;&quot;&gt;T4 (Assessing and Mitigating Transport Impacts)&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;of the London Plan (2021) and policies PP1 (Public Realm), LP7 (Advertisements), LP41 (Liveable Neighbourhoods), and LP42 (Walking and Cycling) of the Hackney Local Plan LP33 (2020).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-50c051a7-7fff-8f23-34a7-afe4e804d495&quot;&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color:rgb(0,0,0);font-family:&amp;quot;PT Sans&amp;quot;,&amp;quot;Helvetica Neue&amp;quot;,Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif;font-size:14px&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
  ],
